Package: GloBIAnalysis
Type: Package
Title: Analysis of the Global Biotic Interactions curated bee-plant datasets
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Beatrice", "Taur", email = "btaur@smith.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")), 
    person("Nelle", "Feliciano", email = "nfeliciano@smith.edu", role = "aut"), 
    person("Meghan", "Gram-Dinger", email = "mgramdinger@smith.edu", role = "aut")
  )
Description: This package is used to analyze the Global Biotic Interactions curated bee-plant datasets. 
    The 3 datasets included in this package examine the interactions between bees and plants across a 
    range of species and geographic distributions. This package contains functions that make it easy for a 
    user to view the summary statistics for the bees and plants included in the data, as well as the geographic
    distribution of the observations and the types of interactions recorded. Interactions between bees and plants
    can be easily visualized using the functions included in this package, and it also enables a simplified ANOVA
    analysis of the affect of bee-plant interactions on bee and plant populations.
Data source: https://zenodo.org/records/18303036
